FajarQuant Phase E — Bilingual Corpus v1.0 — License Attribution NOTICE
=========================================================================

This file accompanies any model derived from training on the
FajarQuant Phase E Bilingual Corpus v1.0 (Indonesian + English).
It records the corpus composition, source licenses, and attribution
requirements that carry forward to derivative models per the
respective source licenses.

Spec reference: docs/FJQ_PHASE_E_BILINGUAL_CORPUS_V1.md
Plan reference: docs/FJQ_PHASE_E_BILINGUAL_KERNEL_PRODUCTION_PLAN.md v1.8

-------------------------------------------------------------------------
Corpus composition
-------------------------------------------------------------------------

This model was pretrained on a bilingual corpus comprising:

  Indonesian half (on-disk parquet shards, post-exact-hash dedup):

    - Wikipedia (Indonesian, snapshot 20231101)
        HF dataset: wikimedia/wikipedia (config 20231101.id)
        License:    Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0
                    International (CC BY-SA 4.0)
        Volume:     662,929 articles / 1.06 GB raw text / ~0.42 B tokens
                    (Mistral v3 32K tokenizer, 2.527 byte/tok)

    - FineWeb-2 (Indonesian Latin script, slice 1)
        HF dataset: HuggingFaceFW/fineweb-2 (config ind_Latn)
        License:    Open Data Commons Attribution License v1.0 (ODC-By 1.0)
        Volume:     9,999,982 documents / 37.86 GB raw text / ~14.99 B tokens
                    (10M-doc first slice; full ind_Latn config not used)

    Subtotal Indonesian: 10,662,911 documents / 38.92 GB raw text /
                         ~15.40 B tokens; 0.0254% exact-hash dedup rate
                         (sha256 over NFKC + lowercase + whitespace-collapse
                         normalized text).

  English half (streaming, no on-disk parquet):

    - SlimPajama-627B Reupload
        HF dataset: gmongaras/SlimPajama-627B_Reupload
        License:    Apache 2.0 (mirror of original SlimPajama; redistribution
                    permitted)
        Volume:     up to 10.27 B tokens at training time, capped per
                    Phase E v1.8 60:40 ID:EN ratio against the 15.40 B
                    Indonesian corpus

  Total bilingual mix at 60:40 ID:EN default ratio:
    25.67 B tokens (15.40 B Indonesian + 10.27 B English)
    Synthetic-mix-ratio: 0% (Lapis 1 only — real corpus, no augmentation)

