-------------------------------------------------------------------------
Reproducibility surface (per plan v1.7 §14.5)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------

The corpus is reproducible from public sources via:

  1. git commit SHA   — fajarkraton/fajarquant repository
  2. eval/HARNESS_SHA — lm-eval pin (currently 27988a293647d5853e48edea291640b4af54740c, v0.4.11)
  3. Per-source manifests at:
       data/phase_e/corpus_id_dedup_exact/HuggingFaceFW__fineweb-2/_manifest.json
       data/phase_e/corpus_id_dedup_exact/wikimedia__wikipedia/_manifest.json
     (committed in repo; contain bytes_text_kept, docs_kept, dedup_rate,
     normalization scheme, sample_dropped)
  4. HF dataset revisions — pinned via streaming default at corpus-build
     time (Wikipedia 20231101 snapshot stable; FineWeb-2 default stable;
     SlimPajama-627B-Reupload stable)

End-to-end regenerable via:

  make build-id-corpus-wikipedia-id   # ~5 min  (665K articles)
  make build-id-corpus-fineweb-2-id   # ~75 min (10M documents)
  make dedup-corpus-id-exact          # ~20 min (sha256 over 10.67M docs)
  make verify-bilingual-corpus        # <1 s   (8/8 invariants)

-------------------------------------------------------------------------
Use-case scope
-------------------------------------------------------------------------

This corpus is the pretrain artifact for Phase E v1.8 Tier 1+2:
  - Tier 1: kernel-context LLM with formal `@kernel`/`@device` isolation
            (FajarOS Nova target)
  - Tier 2: Indonesian + English bilingual ternary embedded LLM

Tier 3 (vertical AI for tax/legal Indonesian) is deferred to Phase F per
plan v1.8; that corpus and any TaxPrime-derived data are NOT part of
this v1.0 release.

